title: Enrollment of postsecondary students in Canada , by age and gender 2017/18
summary: This is a multi-line chart with 2 lines representing Male, and Female. The y axis denotes Number of students and the x axis denotes Year.
Overall Male, and Female are rapidly decreasing,  throughout the Year
Male, and Female has decreased by 99.61912238237495, and 99.82666369748 percent respectively.
The lines ordered according to average values of Number of students in descending order is: 1. Female, and lastly, 2. Male.
Overall across the Year, Female mostly maintained the highest Number of students when compared to others with a mean value of 168751.29, and it peaked at 20_to_24_years.
Male mostly had the least Number of students with a mean value of 132632.57, which peaked at 20_to_24_years with a value of 412731.0.
